headline: Wynn Resorts Stock Is Rising. Here’s What We Know.
summary: Wynn Resorts  the operator of casinos in China’s Macau and in Las Vegas, was rising ahead of the open on Friday.  Moody’s upgraded Wynn’s credit outlook to Positive from Stable, citing a recovery in Macau, while keeping its credit rating unchanged at B1, below investment grade.  Separately, a Securities and Exchange Commission filing showed that Wynn executive Ellen Whittemore will be leaving her role as general counsel and secretary effective Sunday, to be succeeded by Jacqui Krum.
